sample.User

Class Users

  • java.lang.Object
    • sample.User.Users

  • public class Users
extends java.lang.Object
    Class Users is made to organise and control all data about user of the application. This class includes different Array Lists ph, entr1, entr2 a jr. Each of them has 3 methods.
    ph:
    - CreatePhysical()
    - CheckPhysical(String, String)
    - AddorChangePhysical(int, PhysicalPerson)
    ent1:
    - CreateEntrepreneur()
    - CheckEntrepreneur(String, String)
    - AddorChangeEntrepreneur(int, NaturalPersonEntrepreneur1)
    ent2:
    - CreateEntrepreneur2()
    - CheckEntrepreneur2(String, String)
    - AddorChangeEntrepreneur2(int, NaturalPersonEntrepreneur2)
    jr:
    - CreateJuridical()
    - CheckJuridical(String, String)
    - AddorChangeJuridical(int, JuridicalPerson)

      • AddorChangePhysical

        public int AddorChangePhysical(int number,
                               PhysicalPerson physicalPerson)
                        throws java.io.IOException
        Method is made for adding a new physical person after registration or changing an existing one while working in "userpage"
        Parameters:
        number - is an ordinal number of this user in appropriate arraylist (ph), if the user is not in it yet( number = 100) it will just add it to the end.
        physicalPerson - is a user which will be placed to its old place or add to the end
        Returns:
        the method returns ordinal number of user in an appropriate arraylist (ph) work with in while calling this method next time again
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - in case the file is empty.
